=========================Strings==========================
Import java.lang.String ;

String s;  - String is obj in java created by given above class 

Properties :-
          * Immutable , Use StringBuffer, String Builder for mutable strings 
          
          
Declaration :- 
            * Can create obj like 2 types - 1. string literals         Ex. String s;
                                            2. New keyword             Ex. String s=new String("Hello world ");
                                            
 Conversion :
            char ch[]={'s','t','r','i','n','g','s'};    
             String s2=new String(ch)       // char to string 

Funtions :-                             Return Type 

          charAt(int)-                        char
          length()                             int
 boolean  contains(char seq)                boolean
 boolean  IsEmpty()                         boolean
          compare(), 
          concat(String s2),                    String     
 boolean  equals(string s2),                boolean
 Strign[] split( string regex),
          length(),
  String  replace(char old,char new ),
          compareTo(),                      - Lexographical values returm 0 ,1 ,-1 
  String  intern(),   
  int     indexOf()   ;
  
  
  
  
  
String substring(int beginx)     -> returns substring for given begin index.
or-String substring(int x,int y)  -> from x to y

